## WARNING — `claude --continue` IS NOT GUARANTEED

`claude --continue` (or `-c`) opens "the most recent conversation in the
current directory". The "most recent" is decided by mtime of the jsonl file in
`~/.claude/projects/<encoded-cwd>/`.

Why this is dangerous in your situation:
1. You have 13+ sessions in `~/.claude/projects/-root/`. Several were touched
   today (today 2026-04-25): `8416db34` (14:55), `4b7fa8f7` (14:22),
   `4e3dff34` (14:16), `200929f4` (13:32). Mtime can be touched even by
   passive reads or by other Claude tooling.
2. If you accidentally start a NEW empty session (any `claude` command
   without `-r/-c`), it gets a brand-new UUID, becomes "most recent", and
   `--continue` after that lands you in the empty new one instead of here.
3. If you launch any other automated Claude task on this machine, that
   session also competes for "most recent" status.

**Do not rely on `--continue`. Always use `--resume <uuid>` from this file.**

